<p>Is it possible to add a class once you've scrolled to the bottom of a particular element/div?</p>  <p>I have the following that works, it just adds the class when the top of the div.content_activity reaches the top of the browser, when i want it to add when the bottom of the div reaches the top of the browser..</p>  <pre><code>    var footer = $('.product_footer');      $(window).scroll(function () {         var y = $(this).scrollTop();         var z = $('.content_activity').offset().top;          if (y &gt;= z) {             footer.removeClass('fixed_footer').addClass('hidden_footer');         }         else{            footer.removeClass('hidden_footer').addClass('fixed_footer');         }     }); </code></pre>  <p>Tried changing .offset().top; to .offset().bottom; but no luck.</p>  <p>Had a search and couldn't find this asked before, all included a set height from the top of the browser, this is the bottom of an element which could vary in hight from page to page.</p>